LOCKHART POWER COMPANY SCHEDULE RESALE RESALE SERVICE - MUNICIPALITIES Effective --- ____________
AVAILABILITY
Available for Resale purposes to Municipalities operating in the area served by the Company.
This schedule is not available for auxiliary or breakdown service.
The obligations of the Company in regard to supplying power are dependent upon its securing and retaining all necessary rights-of-ways, privileges, franchises and permits, for the delivery of such power, and the Company shall not be liable to any Customer or Applicant for power in the event it is delayed in, or is prevented from furnishing the power by its failure to secure and retain such rights-of-ways, rights, privileges, franchises and permits.
TYPE OF SERVICE
The Company will furnish 60 cycle service through one meter, at one delivery point located inside the corporate limits of a Municipality at whatever voltage is available. Additional delivery points will be provided by separate agreement.
*MONTHLY RATE
Demand Charge for each KW of Billing Demand is *. Energy Charge for each kWH is * Plus Cosac Power Cost Adjustment *Charges Developed in cost of service study attached as Appendix A
ANNUAL COSAC ADJUSTMENT FOR COSTS
The above monthly rate is subject to adjustment May 1 each year for changes in the company's total unit costs, based on previous years costs as detailed in Appendix A. FERC Form 1 reference pages are included in Appendix A for reference in the event that future revisions to Form 1 affect "item source" pages cited in Appendix A.
COSAC POWER COST ADJUSTMENT
The amount computed at the above monthly rate shall be adjusted for demand and energy amounts calculated in accordance with the formula specified in the monthly Power Cost Adjustment Clause which is incorporated as a part of this rate.
DETERMINATION OF BILLING DEMAND
The demand for billing purposes each month shall be the integrated thirty-minute coincident peak demand in the month for which the bill is rendered; but not less than 50 percent of the contract demand, nor less than 50 percent of the highest billing demand during the previous twelve months, including the month for which bill is rendered.
Where more than one meter is used to meter a single customer located entirely on a single contiguous premises, the demand meters will be arithmetically added to determine the monthly demand.
MINIMUM BILL
The monthly minimum bill shall be the highest of $3.93 per KW of billing demand as above determined, $3.93 per KW per month of contract demand, or $3.93 per KW of the maximum monthly demand during the previous 12 months, including the month for which the bill is rendered.
PAYMENT
Bills under this Schedule are due and payable at the office of the Company on or before the tenth day after the date of the bill.
CONTRACT PERIOD
The Company may require a contract for an original term justified by the circumstances, and will thereafter continue it from year to year upon the condition that either party can terminate it at the end of the original term or at any time thereafter by giving at least 60 days previous notice of such termination in writing. The minimum term of contract shall be not less than one year.
RULES AND REGULATIONS
Service under this schedule is subject to orders of governmental bodies having jurisdiction and to the currently effective "General Terms and Conditions" and contract agreements applicable to Rate Schedules under FERC Electric Tariff Original Volume No. 1. Nothing contained herein shall be construed as affecting in any way the right of Lockhart Power Company to unilaterally make application to the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission, or any other regulatory authority having jurisdiction, for a change in rates under Section 205 of the Federal Power Act and pursuant to the Commission's Rules and Regulations promulgated thereunder.
COSAC POWER COST ADJUSTMENT
When the unit cost of power and energy for meeting the requirements of The Company's customer in any month is above or below the base unit cost in cents per kilowatt for the demand portion of the cost and is above or below the base unit cost in cents per kilowatt hour for the energy portion of the cost, the total charges provided for by the above Monthly Rate shall be increased or decreased respectively by the product of customer's billing demand during that month and the factor AD, and the energy delivered to the customer during that month times the factor AE, where factor AD, calculated to the nearest 0.01 cent per kilowatt and factor AE, calculated to the nearest 0.0001 cent per kilowatt hour are determined by the equations below:
+- -+ AD = (PD x RCP/SP) - * + PYA/12 x GRT RBD RBD +- -+
Where AD = Amount of adjustment applied to the month's billing demand in cents per KW. RBD = Resale Customers billing demand this month. PD = Demand portion of the Company's purchased power cost for the month, in cents including all charges except those identified as energy charges. RCP = Resale Customers estimated annual coincident peak demand in KW times 1.07592. SP = The estimated system annual coincident peak demand at production level in KW. * = Demand portion of the purchased power cost included in the monthly rate, allocated to the resale customer, in cents per KW. This base is adjusted annually as detailed in Appendix A. PYA = Difference in PCA demand costs billed in the base prior calendar year and demand costs allocated for that year using the actual annual coincident peak values. GRT = South Carolina gross receipts tax factor. GRT currently is equal to 1.003.
LOCKHART POWER COMPANY SCHEDULE RESALE RESALE SERVICE - MUNICIPALITIES Effective --- __________
+- -+ AE = ((PE+FC-RC) x REP/SE) - * x GRT REM +- -+
Where AE = Amount of adjustment to the month's energy charges, in cents per kWH. PE = Energy portion of the Company's purchased power costs for the month in cents. FC = Fuel Expense for the month in cents. RC = Revenues received for sales from assets for which wholesale customer otherwise bears cost responsibility. REP = Resale Customer's total metered energy purchases for the month in kWH x 1.050. SE = Total system energy input at production level. REM = Resale Customer's total metered energy purchases for the month in kWH. * = Base energy cost included in the monthly rate. This base is adjusted annually as detailed in Appendix A. GRT = South Carolina gross receipts tax factor. GRT currently is equal to 1.003. This adjustment for the month as calculated above shall be added to the billing for the next succeeding month. The RCP/SP ratio shall be estimated at the beginning of each calendar year and may be adjusted during the year in order to minimize the difference in the annual allocated demand costs and annual demand PCA billings.

LOCKHART POWER COMPANY COST OF SERVICE STUDY RESALE REVENUE REQUIREMENT Effective --- _______________
RR = RRT(RB) + EXP + SIT + FIT - AITC(PA)
WHERE,
RR = REVENUE REQUIREMENT
RRT = RATE OF RETURN ON RATE BASE
RB = RATE BASE
EXP = TOTAL EXPENSES EXCLUDING INCOME TAXES
SIT = STATE INCOME TAXES
FIT = FEDERAL INCOME TAXES
AITC = AMORTIZATION OF INVESTMENT TAX CREDIT
PA = SEE APPENDIX A, PAGE 11 OF 19
AND,
RRT = 11.15%
SIT = STR(RR-EXP)
FIT = FTR(RR-EXP-SIT)
STR = South Carolina income tax rate which equals 5.0%.
FTR = Federal income tax rate which equals 34.0%.
THEREFORE,
RR = RRT(RB) + .627EXP - AITC(PA) .627
SIT = .05RR - .05EXP FIT = .323RR - .323EXP
APPENDIX A
LOCKHART POWER COMPANY COST OF SERVICE STUDY NOTES
(A) Total electric plant amount is arithmetic average of beginning and end of year balances. See FERC Form 1, pages 200, 204, 205, 206 and 207.
(B) Total accumulated depreciation and amortization amount is arithmetic average of beginning and end of year balances. See FERC Form 1, page 200 and 219.
(C) Difference between electric plant in Service and accumulated depreciation and amortization.
(D) Total accumulated deferred income taxes is the arithmetic average of beginning of and end of year balances. See FERC Form 1, page 274.
(E) Total prepayments amount is arithmetic average of beginning of and end of year balances. See FERC Form 1, page 111.
(F) Total materials and supplies is arithmetic average of beginning of and end of year balances. See FERC Form 1, page 227.
(G) Working cash allowance is assumed to be zero.
(H) Rate base is arithmetic sum of net plant, accumulated deferred income taxes, prepayments, materials & supplies and working cash allowance.
(I) Steam and Nuclear production costs are separated into demand, energy-fuel, and energy-other components according to traditional cost of service practice.
(J) Hydraulic costs are separated into demand and energy costs as 82.0% demand related costs and 18.0% energy related costs. This relationship will remain fixed at 82% demand related and 18% energy related.
(K) Other Production costs are separated into demand and energy costs by classifying fuel costs as energy costs and all other costs as demand costs.
APPENDIX A
LOCKHART POWER COMPANY COST OF SERVICE STUDY
DESCRIPTION OF ALLOCATORS
D1 - Demand allocator -- Sum of 12 monthly Resale Customer demands coincident with the monthly peak demand of the Company's wholesale power supplier times 1.07592 (fixed demand loss factor) divided by sum of the 12 Company monthly system demands coincident with the wholesale supplier peak demand. See Appendix A, page 12 of 18.
D2 Demand Purchase Allocator -- Resale Customer demand coincident with the annual calendar year peak demand used by the Company's wholesale power supplier to determine the Company's demand bill times 1.07592 (fixed demand loss factor) divided by the Company system demand coincident with the wholesale supplier peak demand. See Appendix A, page 13 of 19.
DA - Distribution plant allocator -- Distribution plant amount is taken directly from the Company's unit property records and allocator DA is derived as Resale Customer's distribution plant as a percentage of total Company distribution plant. See Appendix A, page 13 of 18 and FERC Form 1, pages 206 and 207, line 75.
L1 - Labor ratio allocator -- This allocator effectively functionalizes the item to be allocated into the major cost function and then allocates each function by the appropriate allocator. See Appendix A, page 14 of 18 and FERC Form 1, page 354.
DB - Distribution plant accumulated depreciation allocator -- Distribution plant accumulated depreciation is derived from the Company's books and allocator DB is derived as Resale Customer's distribution plant accumulated depreciation as a percentage of total distribution plant accumulated depreciation. See FERC Form 1, page 219.
DT - Accumulated deferred income taxes allocator -- Derived as Resale Customer's gross plant as a percentage of total gross plant.
PA - This is a labor ratio allocator which effectively functionalizes items into production, transmission and distribution cost; the production and transmission costs are allocated by D1 and distribution costs by DA. See Appendix A, page 15 of 18 and FERC Form 1, page 354. PA is derived as Resale Customer's percentage of the total.
EM - Energy Monthly allocator -- Derived by multiplying 1.050 x Resale Customer's metered monthly purchases in KWH and dividing this product by total system monthly input in KWH. See Appendix A, page 19.
APPENDIX A
LOCKHART POWER COMPANY COST OF SERVICE STUDY
DESCRIPTION OF ALLOCATORS
E1 - Energy allocator -- Derived by multiplying 1.050 x Resale Customer's metered annual purchases in KWH and dividing this product by total system annual input in KWH. See Appendix A, page 16 of 18 and FERC Form 1, pages 310, 311 and 401a.
DC - Customer accounting allocator -- Resale customer accounting expense to be fixed at $2,800 per year. DC is derived as $2,800 as percentage of total Company customer accounting cost. See FERC Form 1, page 322.
DD - Sales expense allocator -- DD is 0.0% for Resale and 100.0% for Retail.
DE - Retail rate case expense allocator -- DE is 100.0% to Retail and 0.0% to Resale.
DF - Resale rate case expense allocator -- DF is 100.0% to Resale and 0.0% to Retail.
RT - Revenue tax allocator -- RT is derived by the ratio of Resale electric operating revenues to total electric operating revenues during the previous year. See FERC Form 1, pages 263 and 300.
MT - Miscellaneous tax allocator -- MT is derived by as Resale customer's percentage of miscellaneous taxes. See Appendix A, page 17 of 18 and FERC Form 1, page 263.
GP - Gross plant allocator -- Derived as Resale Customer's gross plant as a percentage of total gross plant.
